c a diversified holding company engages in the development and deployment of business solutions and products to the retail agriculture and food service markets its portfolio of proprietary patented technologies address the waste in operations logistics and supply chain the company through its subsidiary pioneer products llc recycles plastics from reclaimed retailers’ waste streams remanufactures into new consumer products such as plastic trash cans and sells products in the retail market ecoark holdings inc through its subsidiary zest labs inc provides farmers distributors and grocers a freshness management solution focused on reducing food waste its flagship product is zest fresh which combines realtime prescriptive analytics with iot productlevel monitoring to enable proactive and intelligent decisionmaking at every step of the fresh food supply chain from field to shelf the company through its subsidiary magnolia solar inc engages in the development production and sale of nanotechnologybased thin film solar cell modules ecoark holdings inc was founded in  and is headquartered in rogers arkansas detailed description  south pinnacle hills parkwaysuiterogers ar united statesfounded in  employees phone  ecoarkusacom key executives for ecoark holdings inc mr peter mehring director ceo  president of zest labs age  total annual compensation k compensation as of fiscal year  ecoark holdings inc key developments stephen dacus joins ecoark as general counsel jun   ecoark announced that stephen dacus has joined the company as general counsel in this role he will be responsible for overseeing the company’s legal affairs acquisition structuring and legal diligence and providing counsel to the board of directors ceo and senior management stephen started his legal career as an associate in the dallas texas office of the international law firm kl gates llp immediately prior to joining ecoark stephen was a partner at the national law firm kutak rock llp in the firm’s fayetteville